# TROUBLESHOOTING
###############################################

# ERROR: "Expected IDs to be unique, found duplicates"
# SOLUTION: Delete the existing document first
# DELETE http://localhost:8000/documents/{document_id}
# Then re-upload

# ERROR: Document not found (404)
# SOLUTION: Check document ID
# GET http://localhost:8000/documents

# ERROR: No results in query
# SOLUTION: Verify documents are indexed
# GET http://localhost:8000/stats

###############################################
# NOTES
###############################################

# 1. DOCUMENT IDs:
#    - If you provide document_id in upload, it will use that
#    - If not provided, it will auto-generate based on filename
#    - Always use unique IDs for different documents
#    - Example IDs: "yes-pdf-doc", "meeting-notes-oct-2", "report-v1"

# 2. RE-UPLOADING:
#    - ALWAYS delete the old version first to avoid duplicate errors
#    - The API now has automatic conflict detection
#    - If document exists, you'll get a 409 Conflict error

# 3. SEARCH TYPES:
#    - "hybrid": Combines semantic + keyword (best for most cases)
#    - "semantic": Pure vector similarity (for conceptual queries)
#    - "keyword": BM25 keyword matching (for exact terms)

# 4. FILE LOCATIONS:
#    - Make sure files are in ./docs/ relative to where you run the requests
#    - Or use absolute paths: C:/path/to/your/docs/file.pdf